Federal Reserve Bank of  Dallas  
President  Richard Fisher  speaks about the reasons he voted 
against the central bank's decision to push down longer-term 
interest rates.  Fisher, speaking in Dallas, also discusses the  U.S. economy 
and job market. (Source: Bloomberg)  00:00 FOMC meeting, statement "operation twist"
05:44 Impact of move on mortgages, jobs, inflation
09:41 Previous dissents, operation twist "efficacy"
16:52 "Concerns" about inflation, "Thor's hammer"
20:23 Fisher responds to questions.  Running time 38:00
 